                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>Handsome and distinctive red and blue flourished initials with long borders, enclosing designs of oak and other leaves and wyverns; red or blue initials flourished in the other colour.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>Some early marginal annotation, including profile monks’ faces.</additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding calendar="Gregorian" notAfter="1500" notBefore="1400">
                        <p>s. xv, probably College, heavily restored in modern times: reverse-bevelled bare oak boards, with slightly projecting squares, rebacked with modern vellum; sewn on five bands; original blue and plain endbands; formerly two broad straps from recesses in the front board to catches at the back. Formerly a chain-staple at the foredge of the front board, near the foot.</p>
                     </binding>
